{title: You'd Still Find A Way To Cheat On Me}
{artist: Jean Shepard}
{composer: Written by Jack Rhodes, Billie Jo Spears, Henry Ebner}

[G]I could lock you in a [C]deep darken [G]dungeon
Put a big ball and chain on your [D7]feet
Even [G]dress you in an [C]old suit of [G]armor
You'd still find a [D7]way to cheat on [G]me
